The paper discusses the development of a malware detection system using data mining and machine learning techniques. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as the focus is on detecting and preventing malicious software. The use of machine learning algorithms and data mining techniques also suggests that the paper could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of static analysis to extract features from Windows PE files, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of information gain and principal component analysis suggests that the paper could also be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
